Properties.name: EXCHANGELEGACYINTEROP@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: This group is for interoperability with Exchange 2003 servers within the same forest. This group should not be deleted.

Properties.name: $D31000-NSEL5BRJ63V7@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.distinguishedname: CN=Exchange Install Domain Servers,CN=Microsoft Exchange System Objects,DC=htb,DC=local
Properties.description: This group is used during Exchange setup and is not intended to be used for other purposes.

Properties.name: EXCHANGE WINDOWS PERMISSIONS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.distinguishedname: CN=Exchange Windows Permissions,OU=Microsoft Exchange Security Groups,DC=htb,DC=local
Properties.description: This group contains Exchange servers that run Exchange cmdlets on behalf of users via the management service. Its members have permission to read and modify all Windows accounts and groups. This group should not be deleted.

Properties.name: MANAGED AVAILABILITY SERVERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.distinguishedname: CN=Managed Availability Servers,OU=Microsoft Exchange Security Groups,DC=htb,DC=local
Properties.description: This group contains all the Managed Availability servers. This group shouldn't be deleted.

Properties.name: EXCHANGE TRUSTED SUBSYSTEM@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.distinguishedname: CN=Exchange Trusted Subsystem,OU=Microsoft Exchange Security Groups,DC=htb,DC=local
Properties.description: This group contains Exchange servers that run Exchange cmdlets on behalf of users via the management service. Its members have permission to read and modify all Exchange configuration, as well as user accounts and groups. This group should not be deleted.

Properties.name: EXCHANGE SERVERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: This group contains all the Exchange servers. This group shouldn't be deleted.

Properties.name: SECURITY ADMINISTRATOR@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Membership in this role group is synchronized across services and managed centrally. This role group is not manageable through the administrator portals. Members of this role group may include cross-service administrators, as well as external partner groups and Microsoft Support. By default, this group may not be assigned any roles. However, it will be a member of the Security Administrators role groups and will inherit the capabilities of that role group.

Properties.name: SECURITY READER@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Membership in this role group is synchronized across services and managed centrally. This role group is not manageable through the administrator portals. Members of this role group may include cross-service administrators, as well as external partner groups and Microsoft Support. By default, this group may not be assigned any roles. However, it will be a member of the Security Reader role groups and will inherit the capabilities of that role group.

Properties.name: COMPLIANCE MANAGEMENT@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: This role group will allow a specified user, responsible for compliance, to properly configure and manage compliance settings within Exchange in accordance with their policy.

Properties.name: HYGIENE MANAGEMENT@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this management role group can manage Exchange anti-spam features and grant permissions for antivirus products to integrate with Exchange.

Properties.name: DELEGATED SETUP@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this management role group have permissions to install and uninstall Exchange on provisioned servers. This role group shouldn't be deleted.

Properties.name: DISCOVERY MANAGEMENT@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this management role group can perform searches of mailboxes in the Exchange organization for data that meets specific criteria.

Properties.name: RECORDS MANAGEMENT@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this management role group can configure compliance features such as retention policy tags, message classifications, transport rules, and more.

Properties.name: HELP DESK@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this management role group can view and manage the configuration for individual recipients and view recipients in an Exchange organization. Members of this role group can only manage the configuration each user can manage on his or her own mailbox. Additional  permissions can be added by assigning additional management roles to this role group.

Properties.name: SERVER MANAGEMENT@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this management role group have permissions to manage all Exchange servers within the Exchange organization, but members don't have permissions to perform operations that have global impact in the Exchange organization.

Properties.name: PUBLIC FOLDER MANAGEMENT@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.distinguishedname: CN=Public Folder Management,OU=Microsoft Exchange Security Groups,DC=htb,DC=local
Properties.description: Members of this management role group can manage public folders. Members can create and delete public folders and manage public folder settings such as replicas, quotas, age limits, and permissions as well as mail-enable and mail-disable public folders.

Properties.name: UM MANAGEMENT@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this management role group can manage Unified Messaging organization, server, and recipient configuration.

Properties.name: VIEW-ONLY ORGANIZATION MANAGEMENT@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.distinguishedname: CN=View-Only Organization Management,OU=Microsoft Exchange Security Groups,DC=htb,DC=local
Properties.description: Members of this management role group can view recipient and configuration objects and their properties in the Exchange organization.

Properties.name: RECIPIENT MANAGEMENT@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this management role group have rights to create, manage, and remove Exchange recipient objects in the Exchange organization.

Properties.name: ORGANIZATION MANAGEMENT@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this management role group have permissions to manage Exchange objects and their properties in the Exchange organization. Members can also delegate role groups and management roles in the organization. This role group shouldn't be deleted.

Properties.name: DNSUPDATEPROXY@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: DNS clients who are permitted to perform dynamic updates on behalf of some other clients (such as DHCP servers).

Properties.name: DNSADMINS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: DNS Administrators Group

Properties.name: ENTERPRISE KEY ADMINS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this group can perform administrative actions on key objects within the forest.

Properties.name: KEY ADMINS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this group can perform administrative actions on key objects within the domain.

Properties.name: PROTECTED USERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this group are afforded additional protections against authentication security threats. See http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=298939 for more information.

Properties.name: ENTERPRISE READ-ONLY DOMAIN CONTROLLERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this group are Read-Only Domain Controllers in the enterprise

Properties.name: CLONEABLE DOMAIN CONTROLLERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this group that are domain controllers may be cloned.

Properties.name: READ-ONLY DOMAIN CONTROLLERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this group are Read-Only Domain Controllers in the domain

Properties.name: DENIED RODC PASSWORD REPLICATION GROUP@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members in this group cannot have their passwords replicated to any read-only domain controllers in the domain

Properties.name: ALLOWED RODC PASSWORD REPLICATION GROUP@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members in this group can have their passwords replicated to all read-only domain controllers in the domain

Properties.name: TERMINAL SERVER LICENSE SERVERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this group can update user accounts in Active Directory with information about license issuance, for the purpose of tracking and reporting TS Per User CAL usage

Properties.name: WINDOWS AUTHORIZATION ACCESS GROUP@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this group have access to the computed tokenGroupsGlobalAndUniversal attribute on User objects

Properties.name: INCOMING FOREST TRUST BUILDERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this group can create incoming, one-way trusts to this forest

Properties.name: ACCOUNT OPERATORS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members can administer domain user and group accounts

Properties.name: SERVER OPERATORS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members can administer domain servers

Properties.name: PRE-WINDOWS 2000 COMPATIBLE ACCESS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: A backward compatibility group which allows read access on all users and groups in the domain

Properties.name: RAS AND IAS SERVERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Servers in this group can access remote access properties of users

Properties.name: GROUP POLICY CREATOR OWNERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members in this group can modify group policy for the domain

Properties.name: DOMAIN GUESTS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: All domain guests

Properties.name: DOMAIN USERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: All domain users

Properties.name: CERT PUBLISHERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this group are permitted to publish certificates to the directory

Properties.name: DOMAIN ADMINS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Designated administrators of the domain

Properties.name: ENTERPRISE ADMINS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Designated administrators of the enterprise

Properties.name: SCHEMA ADMINS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Designated administrators of the schema

Properties.name: DOMAIN CONTROLLERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: All domain controllers in the domain

Properties.name: DOMAIN COMPUTERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: All workstations and servers joined to the domain

Properties.name: STORAGE REPLICA ADMINISTRATORS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this group have complete and unrestricted access to all features of Storage Replica.

Properties.name: SYSTEM MANAGED ACCOUNTS GROUP@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this group are managed by the system.

Properties.name: REMOTE MANAGEMENT USERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this group can access WMI resources over management protocols (such as WS-Management via the Windows Remote Management service). This applies only to WMI namespaces that grant access to the user.

Properties.name: ACCESS CONTROL ASSISTANCE OPERATORS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this group can remotely query authorization attributes and permissions for resources on this computer.

Properties.name: HYPER-V ADMINISTRATORS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this group have complete and unrestricted access to all features of Hyper-V.

Properties.name: RDS MANAGEMENT SERVERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Servers in this group can perform routine administrative actions on servers running Remote Desktop Services. This group needs to be populated on all servers in a Remote Desktop Services deployment. The servers running the RDS Central Management service must be included in this group.

Properties.name: RDS ENDPOINT SERVERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Servers in this group run virtual machines and host sessions where users RemoteApp programs and personal virtual desktops run. This group needs to be populated on servers running RD Connection Broker. RD Session Host servers and RD Virtualization Host servers used in the deployment need to be in this group.

Properties.name: RDS REMOTE ACCESS SERVERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Servers in this group enable users of RemoteApp programs and personal virtual desktops access to these resources. In Internet-facing deployments, these servers are typically deployed in an edge network. This group needs to be populated on servers running RD Connection Broker. RD Gateway servers and RD Web Access servers used in the deployment need to be in this group.

Properties.name: CERTIFICATE SERVICE DCOM ACCESS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this group are allowed to connect to Certification Authorities in the enterprise

Properties.name: EVENT LOG READERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this group can read event logs from local machine

Properties.name: CRYPTOGRAPHIC OPERATORS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members are authorized to perform cryptographic operations.

Properties.name: IIS_IUSRS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Built-in group used by Internet Information Services.

Properties.name: DISTRIBUTED COM USERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members are allowed to launch, activate and use Distributed COM objects on this machine.

Properties.name: PERFORMANCE MONITOR USERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this group can access performance counter data locally and remotely

Properties.name: PERFORMANCE LOG USERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members of this group may schedule logging of performance counters, enable trace providers, and collect event traces both locally and via remote access to this computer

Properties.name: REMOTE DESKTOP USERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members in this group are granted the right to logon remotely

Properties.name: NETWORK CONFIGURATION OPERATORS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members in this group can have some administrative privileges to manage configuration of networking features

Properties.name: REPLICATOR@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Supports file replication in a domain

Properties.name: BACKUP OPERATORS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Backup Operators can override security restrictions for the sole purpose of backing up or restoring files

Properties.name: PRINT OPERATORS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Members can administer printers installed on domain controllers

Properties.name: GUESTS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Guests have the same access as members of the Users group by default, except for the Guest account which is further restricted

Properties.name: USERS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Users are prevented from making accidental or intentional system-wide changes and can run most applications

Properties.name: ADMINISTRATORS@HTB.LOCAL
Properties.description: Administrators have complete and unrestricted access to the computer/domain
